The paper deals with algorithmic problems in computer science, specifically online bipartite matching and max-sat. The focus is on the limitations of deterministic de-randomization techniques, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in the analysis of the algorithms. Additionally, the use of submodular maximization and parallelism suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
